-- Alameda County protocols
INSERT INTO protocolChunks (countyId, protocolNumber, protocolTitle, section, content, sourcePdfUrl, createdAt)
SELECT c.id, 'P-1', 'Cardiac Arrest - Adult', 'Cardiac', 'Begin high-quality CPR. Attach AED/monitor. Defibrillate VF/VT at 200J. Epinephrine 1mg IV/IO every 3-5 min. Amiodarone 300mg for refractory VF/VT. Consider reversible causes (Hs and Ts).', '', NOW()
FROM counties c WHERE c.name = 'Alameda County EMS Agency' AND c.state = 'California' LIMIT 1;

INSERT INTO protocolChunks (countyId, protocolNumber, protocolTitle, section, content, sourcePdfUrl, createdAt)
SELECT c.id, 'P-2', 'Stroke', 'Neurological', 'Cincinnati Stroke Scale assessment. Document last known well time. Blood glucose check. Rapid transport to stroke center. Pre-notify receiving facility.', '', NOW()
FROM counties c WHERE c.name = 'Alameda County EMS Agency' AND c.state = 'California' LIMIT 1;

INSERT INTO protocolChunks (countyId, protocolNumber, protocolTitle, section, content, sourcePdfUrl, createdAt)
SELECT c.id, 'P-3', 'Chest Pain - ACS', 'Cardiac', '12-lead ECG. Aspirin 324mg. NTG 0.4mg SL if SBP>90. Morphine for pain. STEMI activation if indicated.', '', NOW()
FROM counties c WHERE c.name = 'Alameda County EMS Agency' AND c.state = 'California' LIMIT 1;

-- San Diego County protocols
INSERT INTO protocolChunks (countyId, protocolNumber, protocolTitle, section, content, sourcePdfUrl, createdAt)
SELECT c.id, 'S-100', 'Patient Assessment', 'General', 'Scene safety, BSI. Primary survey: ABCDE. Secondary survey: head-to-toe. Vital signs. History: SAMPLE, OPQRST.', '', NOW()
FROM counties c WHERE c.name = 'San Diego County EMS' AND c.state = 'California' LIMIT 1;

INSERT INTO protocolChunks (countyId, protocolNumber, protocolTitle, section, content, sourcePdfUrl, createdAt)
SELECT c.id, 'S-130', 'Cardiac Arrest', 'Cardiac', 'High-quality CPR. Early defibrillation. Vascular access. ACLS medications. Post-arrest care.', '', NOW()
FROM counties c WHERE c.name = 'San Diego County EMS' AND c.state = 'California' LIMIT 1;

-- Orange County protocols
INSERT INTO protocolChunks (countyId, protocolNumber, protocolTitle, section, content, sourcePdfUrl, createdAt)
SELECT c.id, 'OC-1', 'Cardiac Arrest - Adult', 'Cardiac', 'CPR, defibrillation, epinephrine, amiodarone. Consider ECMO for refractory arrest.', '', NOW()
FROM counties c WHERE c.name = 'Orange County EMS Agency' AND c.state = 'California' LIMIT 1;

INSERT INTO protocolChunks (countyId, protocolNumber, protocolTitle, section, content, sourcePdfUrl, createdAt)
SELECT c.id, 'OC-2', 'Stroke', 'Neurological', 'Stroke scale, last known well, glucose, rapid transport to comprehensive stroke center.', '', NOW()
FROM counties c WHERE c.name = 'Orange County EMS Agency' AND c.state = 'California' LIMIT 1;
